CARMEN XXIX.

This poem can be dated. Aelius Gallus, the praefect of Egypt, invaded Arabia in 24 B.c. Iccius was plainly preparing to accompany him, so that the ode was written in 25 or 24 B.c. The twelfth Epistle of Book i is addressed to the same Iccius, then agent os Agrippa's Sicilian estate. It is couched in the same ironical tone, and laughs at the gentleman who was divided between an interest in philosophy and the desire for walth.
